THREE
firefighters have been report dead, following the fire at the Department of
Health building. The
cause of the fire is still unknown at this stage. Reportedly
sparks were seen coming from plug points, before the fire started. The
fire broke out on the 24th floor of the building just after 10:00. WATCH:
1 DEAD IN HEALTH DEPARTMENT BUILDING FIRE! "We
are extremely devastated," said Joburg MMC for Public Safety Michael Sun
about the fire that broke out at the Department of Health in Joburg. The
four firefighters that were trapped in the building were rescued. Sun
said two other firefighters who died are those who were trapped inside the
building. “Eight
other firefighters have been admitted to hospital, seven with various degrees
of injured while one was admitted for exhaustion,” Sun said.